Cursor.title: cursor
Cursor.description: A unique identifier (specifically, a [TOID](stellar.org/protocol/sep-35)) that points to a specific location in a collection of responses and is pulled from the `paging_token` value of a record. When a cursor is provided, RPC will _not_ include the element whose ID matches the cursor in the response: only elements which appear _after_ the cursor will be included.
